                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-69-victim544 t18290115-69-viclabel337"></join>. On the 11th of December, about seven o'clock in the evening, I saw the prisoner, with two other boys, near his house, and I watched them - I was on the opposite side of the way; I saw one of them (not the prisoner) reach into Mr. Hull's shop, and take the cap off a book; he put it on the prisoner's head, and they all ran off together<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182901150033"></xptr>- the prisoner had nothing on his head before; I secured him almost immediately, within twenty yards.</p>
